review:
This game has potential and the idea is sound but as of right now it is far too buggy, basic and boring. A lot of content is lacking but the devs plan on adding as time goes on; I will not list the missing promised content since that would add a lot more extra fluff to this review; but basically if you're asking  "is this bit that was promised on kickstarter in yet?  questions, they can currently mostly be answered with "nope". BUT this is an EA game and features should be added down the line; it is still worth noting thou, but i digress;

The good stuff;
- Dinosaur Models are very nice with lots of nice little details
- Animations for the most part are also very well done and the movement system is nice and fluid


The bad / dissapointing stuff;
- The Ai; my god is the AI in this game currently bad, they plan on improving but as of right now it is just slightly better than Arks dinosaurs (little exaggerated but NOT by that much at all); they eat and drink which is neat but for the most part they ignore your existence entirely or if they do aggro to you they only do so momentarily before going back to ignoring you or go off to stand staring into the void. The majesty and wonder of the Hell creek formation ecosystem is dissapointing when the dinos are mindless souless robots standing in a field waiting to die.


This Ai problem leads to the next weakness;
- Difficulty and lack of a sense of achievment;  When the only threat to your survival is the AI creatures and they are too busy stuffing crayons up their own noses the game is an absolute cake walk; i only died when i went and did stupid stuff like attacking an adult trex or trike to see how it would react. Sadly the lack of threat and content leads to the game feeling rather dull and boring since the only thing to do 'late game' as an adult is to explore and see what stupid scenarios the AI can get itself into.

-Environemt; currently is empty and not interesting, lighting issues and lack of many animal species currently makes the world you're living in feel empty even if accurate. I would like to see the environment be improved graphically since it is something you will be staring at for the entirty of your play time, you can have all the scientifically accurate plants you want but if its just plain ugly to look at most of the time (especially at night with the current contrast) it doesnt enthrall me to explore the world you've built.

- Performance & bugs; Performance across the board for this game is poor, massive frame drops and stuttering especially during dusk and night time transitions. Major area to improve on. Lots of bugs too, worth mentioning even if an early access game.



This game has a lot of potential to be a fun and educational game for people interested in dinosaurs, I hope the devs will improve and deliver the promised features and improvements and hopefully that will change this review to a positive one, but currently I just can't recommend this title. If you are interested in it; I would recommend to hold off your purchase until it has improved
